I was goofing around with the new snare drum tonight,  and switched
the hoops to die cast. In order to hear I recorded a bit of playing
through the Mackie into Sonar. The drum sounds pretty good, in all
honesty. So I recorded a drum part to a Steve Perry tune (no previous
drum track), and mixed it down. It came out alright, though it was
pretty tough to match the effects on the album. I also mixed the snare
a tad hot, to hear how it sounds. As an engineer, I make a good
drummer...

But I was very pleased to hear how good the cross-stick sounds. I
would post an MP3, but I don't have any web space available right at
the moment. Anyone have any ideas where I can put the thing? The file
is just under 4 MB.

Thanks.

