Well, I think I might like to hear the drum with wood hoops on it, but
all-in-all I had only played it for about an hour before I recorded
that. I just got it via Fed-Ex yesterday, and after playing it only
about 15-20 minutes I changed out the triple-flanged hoop to the
diecast hoops from a Gretsch snare (thanks Jay!) that I haven't been
playing  much lately. I am not sure if I like the diescast hoops
better or not. I think Pat is playing his with CDB and we are going to
hear them tomorrow--so we'll see how his sounds miked.

I was having fun with Sonar when I recorded that track. I simply
placed loop markers at the beginning and end of the tune and let it
loop. I think that was the second take. I tell you the power of these
DAW programs is simply incredible for what you pay. Just playing
around with the track for an hour in Sonar, I was able to get some
fairly decent effects on the kit. I may spend a little more time to
see if I can get it to blend a bit more nicely--it's a neat learning
exercise, if nothing else.

