Thanks for checking it out...

You know, I almost think there might be an issue with the kick channel
in my board; or with the peak light, more specifically. I agree with
you--the level is low. But if I set the pre-amp gain where it needs to
be to get a hot enough level...then the clip light comes on! I do not
hear any distortion however, and the waveform *seems* to be of the
proper amplitude in SONAR. But the damn idiot light perplexes me a
bit. It's hitting peak (according to the light on the channel) on
nearly every kick note. I am using an Audix D6 by the way, but I
suppose I could back the mic off a tad. I think it's about 10 inches
from the batter head (inside the kick) now.

I do have another D6 on the 16&quot; drum, and I have tried swapping the
two--but get the exact same issue. The peak light comes on. I guess as
long as it doesn't distort, it's  probably OK. I will try to remix the
tune a bit, and maybe EQ the snare. There's only reverb and a tad bit
of compression on it now. As I mentioned, I am trying to learn the art
of recording drums and the slope of the learning curve is quite steep
on certain days. And I really only played around for about an hour
last night, so there is certainly room for improvement.

One cool thing is the automation in SONAR. On this tune the
cross-stick sounds were too soft and so when I turned them up to the
proper level, the snare was HONKING, lol. So I simply automated the
fader control and voila--0db threshold on the crossstick and -6db on
the snare hits. Man, taking the time to learn this software was one of
the best things I ever did.

TB
