Wow Chris, great compliments...coming from a guy with playing
credentials such as yours. I appreciate it!

You are correct about the snare level--it is too loud. That's the
purpose of the experiment (or that's how it started out anyway), to
hear the snare on tape. But the snare is too loud in the mix, for all
practical purposes. Basically I over-EQ'd it, and now the level is too
honking. Easily fixed for the most part.

Now that I listen back to it, I actually don't like the second take as
much as I thought I did. I think the effects are a bit overstated. But
it was indeed just an exercise, so maybe by hearing that now...the
exercise was valuable and I am actually learning something? I'd like
to think so anyway. I would encourage anyone truly interested in
becoming a better drummer to record themselves and pick their playing
apart. Not to obsess about each and every note, but (among other
reasons) to gain an appreciation of how a tune should be structured
and how the drums really fit into that structure. I guess that's the
value of a good producer--someone who sees the big picture in the
tune, and how each instrument fits into that sonic picture.

Thanks again Chris.

